claim.claim-text:
The assembly of a catheter (10) and an endoscope (60),
the catheter comprising: a shaft (16) having a proximal end, a distal end, and a wire guide lumen extending through at least a portion thereof; and a plurality of intermediate wire guide access ports (44) through a side wall of the shaft for providing access to the wire guide lumen, the intermediate wire guide access ports located between and spaced apart from the proximal and distal ends, the endoscope having a working channel extending between a distal port and a proximal port;
characterised by the catheter being so adapted that the plurality of intermediate wire guide access ports are accessible outside the endoscope when the catheter is positioned through the working channel such that the distal end of the catheter and the distal port of the working channel are aligned; and that location of the respective intermediate wire guide access ports near the proximal port of the endoscope corresponds with respective, different, predetermined lengths of the catheter extending beyond the distal port of the endoscope.
